{
  "signal_description": "Calculate the average clearing time for accounts receivable transactions and group the results by customer. The query is performed on the 'defaultview-197' table. The columns used in the query are 'case_id', 'AR_CustomerName', 'ClearingJournalEntry', 'BillingDocument', 'event_name', and 'end_time'. The average clearing time is calculated by subtracting the first end time of the 'Create Billing Request (DMR)' event from the current end time, for each billing document. Only accounts receivable transactions with a non-null customer name and the event name 'Clear Accounts Receivable' are considered. The results are sorted in descending order of the average clearing time and limited to the top 10 records."
}
